Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-grey pottery vessel, the fabric contains a number of small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and very faint traces of a black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393998) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393998)
